column386: New HIV infections - female (number of people)
New HIV infections for males in a given year (number of people)
New HIV infections is defined as the number of people who have been newly infected with HIV (human immunodeficiency virus) in a given year.
New female HIV infections is defined as the number of women who have been newly infected with HIV (human immunodeficiency virus) in a given year.
New male HIV infections is defined as the number of men who have been newly infected with HIV (human immunodeficiency virus) in a given year.
